      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The answer is that the \"tough on crime\" approach is a double-edged sword; while it can temporarily lower crime rates by increasing prison populations, it often disproportionately harms marginalized communities through systemic bias and mass incarceration. However, the real solution lies in combining strict sentencing with robust community investment and restorative justice programs that address the root causes of crime. Without these complementary measures, harsh laws alone will fail to create lasting public safety and will continue to deepen social inequalities.",
